Technology Brief -- International Business Machines:
   Unit to Form Joint Venture
   With Tokyo Software Firms
Employing 54 people, the venture is projected to generate
450 million yen in revenue for the fiscal year beginning
April 1, and is seen posting 2.22 billion yen in annual
revenue after six years.
   Although Japan's banks and securities houses are now
operating in a harsher environment compared with the boom
years of the late 1980s, IBM is confident that the joint
venture will see strong demand, an IBM Japan spokesman said.
"The efficient flow of information is crucial to financial
companies" and will become more so as Japan continues to
liberalize its money markets, he said.